          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_Access_UpdateUserRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to update the roles associated with a user in a Microsoft SQL Server database. It takes an XML input of role names and an authenticated user ID, then updates the user's roles in the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "aspnet_UsersInRoles",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " table based on the provided roles. The procedure ensures that only the specified roles are associated with the user, removing any roles not included in the input and adding any new roles that are not already associated."
        }
      ]
    },
